# =============================================================================
# Root .dockerignore — SAAS-1 (ADR-F058): the api/ingest-worker/arq-worker
# build context is now the REPO ROOT (api/Dockerfile needs `COPY skills/
# /skills/`, which lives outside api/). gateway/ and web/ keep their own
# per-directory .dockerignore (unaffected — those builds still use ./gateway
# and ./web as context).
#
# This file is LOAD-BEARING for build performance, not just hygiene: with a
# root context, an unrelated change anywhere in the tree (docs, evidence
# packs, node_modules) would otherwise bust Docker's context hash and force a
# resend of gigabytes to the daemon on every build. Keep it lean; api/Dockerfile
# only ever COPYs api/{pyproject.toml,README.md,app/,alembic.ini,alembic/,
# entrypoint.sh} and skills/ — everything else here is noise for that build.
# =============================================================================

# ----- VCS -----
.git/
.github/

# ----- Not needed by the api image build -----
# (gateway/web/bridges build from their own contexts with their own
# .dockerignore files — none of their sources belong in THIS context.)
gateway/
web/
word-addin/
slack-bridge/
teams-bridge/
docs/
sample-documents/
deploy/
tests/
api/tests/
scripts/
.vite/
.claude/

# ----- macOS Finder duplicate files (see api/.dockerignore for the "why") -----
**/* [0-9].*
**/* [0-9][0-9].*
**/.DS_Store
**/._*

# ----- Python build / test caches -----
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ----- Node -----
**/node_modules/

# ----- Editor / OS detritus -----
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/

# ----- Secrets — never sent to the build daemon -----
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/*.env
**/*.env.*
!**/*.env.example
# Live gateway config can carry provider routing details; only the .example
# seed is tracked, but exclude the real thing defensively.
gateway.yaml
.envrc

# ----- Misc -----
*.log
